name: Conscious Connected Breathwork by Ram
description: Join us for a conscious connected breathwork session to unwind.  Now you may ask what is conscious connected breathwork? CCB is a breathing technique that involves deep diaphragmatic breathing without any pauses for 30 - 40 minutes  under supervision by a trainer facilitator. The benefits of CCB are many, such as  - better metabolism, emotional awareness, clarity and focus, and enhanced intuition.What to expect from the workshop  - - Grounding Activities- ⁠Cacao ceremony - ⁠Brief talk on Breath as Medicine- ⁠Conscious Connected Breathwork- ⁠Integration activities

name: Movie Under the Stars | Screening: 2 Days in Paris (2007)
description: Open-air screening with a three-course dinner & popcorn "2 Days in Paris" is a romantic comedy-drama that follows the tumultuous relationship of Marion (Julie Delpy) and Jack (Adam Goldberg), a couple attempting to rekindle their romance during a brief stay in Paris. Marion, a French photographer, and Jack, an American interior designer, plan to spend two days in Paris after a vacation in Venice. Their visit is intended to strengthen their bond, but instead, it exposes the cracks in their relationship.Through witty dialogue and humorous situations, "2 Days in Paris" explores themes of love, trust, and the complexities of modern relationships. The film combines the charm of Paris with the raw, unfiltered portrayal of a couple trying to bridge their emotional gaps, ultimately questioning whether their love can withstand the pressures and revelations of their brief stay in the City of Lights.Menu also to be announcedTerms and Conditions:The management is not responsible for any injury or damage that may occur during the event.No liability or claims arising from the consumption or intake of any food or drink will be entertained by the management.Parking near the event premises is at the risk of the vehicle owner.Valet service is available at a charge of Rs. 200 per vehicle.Photographs and videos of ticket holders may be uploaded to social media. name: Family Movie Night | Screening: Zootopia (2016)
description: Family Movie Night: World Cinema for Kids!Screening: Zootopia (2016)"Zootopia" is an animated adventure-comedy set in the vibrant, animal-inhabited metropolis of Zootopia. The film follows Judy Hopps (voiced by Ginnifer Goodwin), a determined and optimistic rabbit who dreams of becoming the first rabbit police officer in the city. Despite graduating top of her class at the police academy, Judy is initially assigned to meter maid duty by Chief Bogo (voiced by Idris Elba), who doubts her capabilities due to her small size.___Join us as we watch a series of carefully curated rare masterpieces from around the world, made just for kids. Watch this while cozying up with your family at the studio.Event HighlightsBroaden Horizons with Global Tales: Dive into diverse artistic expressions through rare masterpieces curated for children. Cultivate Cultural Curiosity: Spark interest in world cinema and inspire exploration of different cultures through film's enchantment. Quality Family Bonding: Embark on a cinematic journey to a new country each month, forging lasting memories and strengthening family connections.Why Attend?Uncover Hidden Treasures: Discover lesser-known gems handpicked for their artistic brilliance and captivating storytelling. Artistic Excellence: Immerse your child in films of unparalleled artistic merit, fueling their imagination and creativity. Safe Family Environment: Enjoy movies in a secure, family-friendly setting, ensuring a worry-free experience for kids and parents alike.Don't miss this opportunity to create lasting memories with your family while exposing your kids to the wonders of world cinema. Join us for Family Movie Night – where the magic of storytelling knows no bounds!Terms and Conditions:The management is not responsible for any injury or damage that may occur during the event.Management will entertain no liability or claims arising from the consumption or intake of any food or drink.Parking near the event premises is at the risk of the vehicle owner.Children above the age of 3 need a ticket to attend the event.Valet service is available at a charge of Rs. 200 per vehicle.Photographs and videos of ticket holders may be uploaded to social media.If you prefer not to be featured, please inform our team.Tickets are non-refundable in case of cancellation or no-show.The movie will take place in the studio

name: Kids Playdate | Gajapati Comes to Courtyard!
description: Ticket Includes All Activities by The LooRoo Club for One Kid and One accompanying parentTrumpeting with all his might,Bringing flowers, fun, and antics,Our little Gajapati is ready for a play date with us!Join us on Sunday, July 14thFrom 10:30 AM to 12:00 PM Who is it for? Children aged 2 - 4 years accompanied by one adult who can join in the play alongside their child at no additional cost.About the PlaydateWe’ll kick off our fun by reading the beloved book Gajapati Kulapati by Ashok Rajagopalan. After the story, we’ll dive into nature-based, sensory, and messy activities inspired by Gajapati's adventures:•⁠ ⁠Build a cozy house for Gajapati•⁠ ⁠Make a special remedy for his cold•⁠ ⁠Give Gajapati a refreshing bath•⁠ ⁠Help his tummy feel better with a fun activityThere will be flower garland sewing, sensory trays for little elephants to play in slush, elephant pot painting, and collage crafts. We’ll also learn about the importance of elephants in our jungles and explore beautiful products made from elephant poop!Don’t miss this exciting play date! It’s going to be full of fun, adventure, and a wonderful way to bring this favourite story to life.Terms and ConditionsThe management bears no responsibility for any injury or damage incurred during the event.Purchase tickets exclusively from the designated ticketing platform.No refunds for no-shows or cancellations under any circumstances.Tickets are non-transferable and intended for personal use only.Event schedule and menu subject to change in case of emergencies or events beyond our control.The management will not entertain liability claims arising from the consumption of food or beverages.Parking near the event venue is at the vehicle owner's risk. name: Mental Health Circle on General Well-Being
description: What are Circles:Circles are small-group, private gatherings to share mental health struggles, connect with others, and learn from shared experiences.Each circle is moderated by the Mindhouse team or verified Circle hosts to ensure everyone feels respected, heard, and valued throughout the discussion. We value confidentiality, mutual respect and trust. We do not disclose participant information beyond the Circle - and you can choose what personal information you’d like to share.- Share your struggles with mental health in a group where people have had similar experiences- Learn from others’ lived experiences and find the right resources to prioritize your well-being- Inspire others to take the next step in their mental health journeyIf you have struggled with mental health, join us for our upcoming Circle on Mental Health on 14 July 2024, sunday at Dialogues cafe, Koramangala or share it with a friend/family member who might need a safe space to share.
